  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a user, I want to know which eth1 endpoint is currently active when some of the configured endpoint are reported INVALID. \r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Should be clear to users which is the current used endpoint\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce\r\n1. configure multiple eth1 endpoints\r\n2. make one of the endpoints failing\r\n3. when warnings similar to `13:13:30.439 WARN  - Endpoint <host>:<port> [1] is INVALID | eth1: Temporary failure in name` appear\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nadd information in the warnings log about the first endpoint currently VALID. Print an additional ERROR in case no endpoints are alive.\r\n\r\n",
